-- Geological Disasters Killed 65 People in China Last Month, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-19T14:58:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/geological-disasters-killed-65-people-in-china-last-month-xinhua-reports.html
Landslides, cave-ins, mudslides and
other geological disasters killed 65 people in China last month,
Xinhua News Agency said, citing the China Institute of Geo-
Environment Monitoring.  A further 30 people went missing in the 33 fatal disasters,
which injured 28 people, Xinhua said, citing a report release by
the institute today. Economic losses were 343 million yuan, the
news agency said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  